@startuml
title ETR Study API — request path across layers (internal overview)

' Main flow is vertical; inner components per layer are stacked vertically
' (not side-by-side) so the diagram stays narrower.
top to bottom direction
scale max 980 width

actor "HTTP client" as Client

package "API layer — app/api" as Api {
  [FastAPI routers] as Router
  [Pydantic request/response] as Schema
  Router -[hidden]down- Schema
}

package "Application — app/services, app/validation" as AppLayer {
  [Services] as Service
  [Validation at boundary] as Val
  Service -[hidden]down- Val
}

package "Persistence — app/repositories, app/core" as PerLayer {
  [Repositories] as Repo
  [Session / unit of work] as UoW
  Repo -[hidden]down- UoW
}

database "SQLite\n(study_app.db)" as Db

Client --> Router : HTTPS / JSON
Router --> Schema : bind, validate,\nmap errors → HTTP
Router --> Service : call use case
Service --> Val : enforce rules\nwhere boundary checks apply
Service --> Repo : read / write
Repo --> UoW : ORM operations
UoW --> Db : SQL

note bottom of Router
  Declares OpenAPI and status codes;
  does not hold business rules.
end note

note bottom of Service
  Business logic and orchestration;
  keeps persistence behind repositories.
end note

@enduml
